Troubleshooting Tips
Permission Denied for Packet Capture:

Ensure user is in wireshark group: groups $USER
Re-login or use newgrp wireshark
Check interface permissions: ls -l /dev/net/tun
PyShark Import Errors:

Install pyshark: pip3 install pyshark
Install tshark: sudo apt install tshark
Verify tshark path: which tshark
No Packets Captured:

Verify interface is up: ip link show
Check capture filter syntax
Ensure traffic generation is running
Try capturing on 'any' interface
Visualization Not Displaying:

Install matplotlib: pip3 install matplotlib networkx
Check X11 forwarding if using SSH
Save to file instead of displaying: plt.savefig()
Conclusion
This lab provided hands-on experience with network traffic analysis using industry-standard tools. Students learned to capture packets with Wireshark/tshark, process network data programmatically, visualize communication patterns, and automate the entire analysis pipeline. These skills are essential for security analysis, network troubleshooting, and understanding product network behavior. The automation scripts developed can be adapted for continuous monitoring and real-time threat detection in production environments.
